gh Hornets\n| AHL\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 60\n| 4\n| 0\n| 4.00\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1964\u201365\n| Pittsburgh Hornets\n| AHL\n| 4\n| 1\n| 3\n| 240\n| 15\n| 0\n| 3.75\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1965\u201366\n| Detroit Red Wings\n| NHL\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 54\n| 2\n| 0\n| 2.22\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1966\u201367\n| Pittsburgh Hornets\n| AHL\n| 9\n| 8\n| 1\n| 541\n| 15\n| 1\n| 1.66\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | NHL Totals\n! 5\n! 1\n! 3\n! 274\n! 11\n! 0\n! 2.41\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bob Bassen]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{icehockeystats|legends=18421}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bassen, Hank}}\n[[Category:1932 births]]\n[[Category:2009 deaths]]\n[[Category:Buffalo Bisons (AHL) players]]\n[[Category:Calgary Stampeders (WHL) players]]\n[[Category:Calgary Wranglers coaches]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey coaches]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey goaltenders]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Chicago Blackhawks players]]\n[[Category:Cincinnati Wings players]]\n[[Category:Detroit Red Wings players]]\n[[Category:Edmonton Flyers (WHL) players]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Alberta]]\n[[Category:Medicine Hat Tigers players]]\n[[Category:Pittsburgh Hornets players]]\n[[Category:Pittsburgh Penguins players]]\n[[Category:Seattle Americans players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Calgary]]\n[[Category:Springfield Indians players]]\n[[Category:Vancouver Canucks (WHL) players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| image = \n| image_size = 230px\n| caption =\n| alt =\n| position = [[Goaltender]]\n| catches = Left\n| height_ft = 5\n| height_in = 10\n| weight_lb = 180\n| played_for = [[Chicago Blackhawks|Chicago Black Hawks]]<br>[[Pittsburgh Penguins]]<br>[[Detroit Red Wings]]\n| league = [[National Hockey League|NHL]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1932|12|6|}}\n| birth_place = [[Calgary, Alberta]], Canada\n| death_date = {{death date and age|mf=yes|2009|5|29|1932|12|6}}\n| death_place = [[Calgary, Alberta]], Canada\n| career_start = 1954\n| career_end = 1968\n}}\n'''Henry \"Hank, Red\" Bassen''' (December 6, 1932 \u2013 May 29, 2009) was a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[ice hockey]] [[goaltender]]. Bassen served as a back-up goaltender in the [[National Hockey League]] for the [[Chicago Blackhawks|Chicago Black Hawks]], [[Detroit Red Wings]] and [[Pittsburgh Penguins]]. He was the father of [[Bob Bassen]] who played 765 regular seasons games in the NHL.\n\n==Playing career==\nBassen began his NHL career in 1954 with the Chicago Black Hawks where he spent two seasons as back-up to [[Al Rollins]]. Bassen went on to have starting roles in the [[Western Hockey League (minor pro)|Western Hockey League]] for the [[Calgary Stampeders]], [[Seattle Americans]] and the [[Vancouver Canucks (WHL)|Vancouver Canucks]] before moving to the Detroit Red Wings where over three seasons he would serve as back-up to [[Terry Sawchuk]] between 1960 and 1963.\n\nDuring the 1963\u201364 season, Bassen played seven games with the [[Cincinnati Wings|Indianapolis Capitals/Cincinnati Wings]] in the [[Central Hockey League (1963\u20131984)|CPHL]] and 26 games with the [[Pittsburgh Hornets]] in the [[American Hockey League|AHL]].<ref>http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=235</ref>\n\nAfter spending most of the season with the [[Pittsburgh Hornets]], Bassen returned to the Red Wings roster to serve back-up once more, this time to [[Roger Crozier]] during the [[1963\u201364 NHL season]]. He played one final year with the [[Pittsburgh Penguins]], backing up [[Les Binkley]] before retiring in 1968.\n\nAfter retiring Bassen managed the junior [[Calgary Wranglers]] from 1984 to 1986 and had two sons go on to play professional hockey.\n\nBassen died on May 29, 2009 of heart failure at age 76.<ref>[http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=424368&int Ex-NHL goalie Hank Bassen dies at 76]</ref>\n\n==Awards and achievements==\n*WCJHL Second All-Star Team (1950)\n*WCJHL First All-Star Team (1952)\n*[[Ontario Hockey Association|OHA]]-Sr. First All-Star Team (1954)\n*[[Western Hockey League (minor pro)|WHL]] First All-Star Team (1960)\n*Outstanding Goaltender Award (fewest goals against - WHL) (1960)\n*Leader Cup (MVP - WHL) (co-winner - ''[[Guyle Fielder]]'') (1960)\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Regular season===\n{| BORDER=\"0\" CELLPADDING=\"1\" CELLSPACING=\"0\" width=\"75%\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! Season\n! Team\n! League\n! GP\n! W\n! L\n! T\n! MIN\n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|GA]]\n! [[Shutout|SO]]\n! [[Goals against average|GAA]]\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1954\u201355 NHL season|1954\u201355]]\n| [[Chicago Blackhawks]]\n| [[National Hockey League|NHL]]\n| 21\n| 4\n| 9\n| 8\n| 1260\n| 63\n| 0\n| 3.00\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1954\u201355 AHL season|1954\u201355]]\n| [[Buffalo Bisons]]\n| [[American Hockey League|AHL]]\n| 37\n| 13\n| 19\n| 5\n| 2220\n| 121\n| 3\n| 3.27\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1955\u201356 NHL season|1955\u201356]]\n| Chicago Blackhawks\n| NHL\n| 12\n| 2\n| 9\n| 1\n| 720\n| 41\n| 1\n| 3.42\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1955\u201356 AHL season|1955\u201356]]\n| Buffalo Bisons\n| AHL\n| 53\n| 26\n| 23\n| 4\n| 3300\n| 201\n| 0\n| 3.65\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1956\u201357\n| [[Calgary Stampeders (ice hockey)|Calgary Stampeders]]\n| [[Western Hockey League (1952\u20131974)|WHL]]\n| 68\n| 29\n| 35\n| 4\n| 4125\n| 223\n| 5\n| 3.24\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1957\u201358\n| [[Seattle Totems|Seattle Americans]]\n| WHL\n| 60\n| 27\n| 27\n| 6\n| 3600\n| 184\n| 3\n| 3.07\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1958\u201359 AHL season|1958\u201359]]\n| [[Springfield Indians]]\n| AHL\n| 29\n| 13\n| 14\n| 2\n| 1740\n| 102\n| 2\n| 3.52\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1959\u201360\n| [[Vancouver Canucks (WHL)|Vancouver Canucks]]\n| WHL\n| 70\n| 44\n| 19\n| 6\n| 4220\n| 172\n| 5\n| 2.45\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1960\u201361 NHL season|1960\u201361]]\n| [[Detroit Red Wings]]\n| NHL\n| 34\n| 13\n| 12\n| 9\n| 2120\n| 98\n| 0\n| 2.77\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1961\u201362 NHL season|1961\u201362]]\n| Detroit Red Wings\n| NHL\n| 27\n| 9\n| 12\n| 6\n| 1620\n| 75\n| 3\n| 2.78\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1961\u201362 EPHL season|1961\u201362]]\n| [[Sudbury Wolves]]\n| [[Eastern Professional Hockey League (1959\u20131963)|EPHL]]\n| 3\n| 1\n| 2\n| 0\n| 180\n| 14\n| 0\n| 4.67\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1961\u201362\n| [[Edmonton Flyers]]\n| WHL\n| 9\n| 4\n| 4\n| 1\n| 557\n| 30\n| 0\n| 3.23\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1962\u201363 NHL season|1962\u201363]]\n| Detroit Red Wings\n| NHL\n| 16\n| 6\n| 5\n| 5\n| 960\n| 52\n| 0\n| 3.25\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1962\u201363 AHL season|1962\u201363]]\n| [[Pittsburgh Hornets]]\n| AHL\n| 40\n| 15\n| 23\n| 2\n| 2400\n| 134\n| 2\n| 3.35\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1963\u201364 NHL season|1963\u201364]]\n| Detroit Red Wings\n| NHL\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 0\n| 60\n| 4\n| 0\n| 4.00\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1963\u201364 CPHL season|1963\u201364]]\n| [[Cincinnati Wings|Indianapolis Capitols / Cincinnati Wings]]\n| [[Central Hockey League (1963\u20131984)|CPHL]]\n| 7\n| 0\n| 6\n| 1\n| 420\n| 39\n| 0\n| 5.57\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1963\u201364 AHL season|1963\u201364]]\n| Pittsburgh Hornets\n| AHL\n| 26\n| 9\n| 15\n| 2\n| 1560\n| 82\n| 1\n| 3.15\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1964\u201365 AHL season|1964\u201365]]\n| Pittsburgh Hornets\n| AHL\n| 57\n| 24\n| 25\n| 7\n| 3433\n| 182\n| 2\n| 3.18\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1965\u201366 NHL season|1965\u201366]]\n| Detroit Red Wings\n| NHL\n| 11\n| 3\n| 3\n| 0\n| 406\n| 17\n| 0\n| 2.51\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1966\u201367 NHL season|1966\u201367]]\n| Detroit Red Wings\n| NHL\n| 8\n| 2\n| 4\n| 0\n| 384\n| 22\n| 0\n| 3